cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.DS, cs.PL, cs.DL

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses debugging distributed systems and proposes an interactive debugger for such systems.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper discusses the implementation of a software tool (the interactive debugger) for distributed systems.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the Global Object Tracker (GoT) programming model, which involves data structures and algorithms for distributed systems.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also less likely but possible as the paper discusses the GoT programming model, which is a new programming language for distributed systems.
- cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is unlikely but possible as the paper discusses the implementation of a browser-based interactive debugger, which could be relevant to digital libraries that use web-based interfaces.
